Heat oven to 300 degrees F. Spray bottom of 9-inch springform pan with no-stick cooking spray. Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter; sprinkle evenly into bottom of pan. Beat cream cheese until fluffy in large bowl. Mix in cocoa and flour. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into prepared pan. Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until center is set. Cool. Chill. Garnish as desired.